  "body": "### Component\n\nAnvil\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (c835a3d 2023-07-17T00:21:00.033122754Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Operating System\n\nNone\n\n### Describe the bug\n\n[This](https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blame/1be8787cc3e12f813b068140675ee274d5bfae81/anvil/src/eth/api.rs#L1433-L1435) `sleep` should be replaced with the logic from [evm_set_next_block_timestamp](https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blame/1be8787cc3e12f813b068140675ee274d5bfae81/anvil/src/eth/api.rs#L1663).\r\n\r\nThe logic should be something like:\r\n\r\n- mine a block\r\n- if `interval` is set:\r\n    - get timestamp of the latest block\r\n    - `self.backend.time().set_next_block_timestamp(last_timestamp + interval)`\r\n- repeat until all blocks mined",
